4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR STANDARDIZATION OF SUBSTANTIAL
5 EQUIVALENCY DETERMINATIONS IN PROFESSIONAL LICENSING; PROVIDING A DEFINITION;
6 REMOVING DUPLICATIVE SUBSECTIONS RELATED TO EQUIVALENCY AND RECIPROCITY; AMENDING
7 SECTIONS 37-1-302, 37-1-304, 37-26-201, 37-33-405, 37-50-203, AND 37-73-204, MCA; AND REPEALING
8 SECTIONS 37-39-203 AND 37-65-310, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 37-1-302, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "37-1-302. Definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions apply:
14 (1) "Board" means a licensing board created under Title 2, chapter 15, that regulates a profession
15 or occupation and that is administratively attached to the department as provided in 2-15-121.
16 (2) "Complaint" means a written allegation filed with a board that, if true, warrants an injunction,
17 disciplinary action against a licensee, or denial of an application submitted by a license applicant.
18 (3) "Department" means the department of labor and industry.
19 (4) "Inspection" means the periodic examination of premises, equipment, or procedures or of a
20 practitioner by the department to determine whether the practitioner's profession or occupation is being
21 conducted in a manner consistent with the public health, safety, and welfare.
22 (5) "Investigation" means the inquiry, analysis, audit, or other pursuit of information by the
23 department, with respect to a written complaint or other information before a board, that is carried out for the
24 purpose of determining:
25 (a) whether a person has violated a provision of law justifying discipline against the person;
26 (b) the status of compliance with a stipulation or order of the board;
27 (c) whether a license should be granted, denied, or conditionally issued; or
28 (d) whether a board should seek an injunction.
