1 (6) "License" means permission granted under a chapter of this title to engage in or practice at a
2 specific level in a profession or occupation, regardless of the specific term used for the permission, including
3 permit, certificate, recognition, or registration.
4 (7) "Profession" or "occupation" means a profession or occupation regulated by a board.
5 (8) (a) “Substantial equivalency” or “substantially equivalent” means that the education,
6 examination, and experience requirements contained in the statutes and rules of another jurisdiction are
7 comparable to or exceed the education, examination, and experience requirements contained in the licensing
8 provisions of a profession or occupation under Title 37. When ascertaining substantial equivalency, the
9 respective board or the department, as applicable, shall consider the qualifications without regard to the
10 sequence in which the experience, education, and examination requirements were attained.
11 (b) For occupations and professions under the authority of a board, the board shall determine
12 substantial equivalency.
13 (c) For occupations and professions under the authority of a department program, the department
14 shall determine substantial equivalency."
