16 Section 2. Section 37-1-304, MCA, is amended to read:
17 "37-1-304. Licensure of out-of-state applicants by endorsement -- reciprocity. (1) Except as
18 provided in Title 37, chapter 39, the board shall issue a license to practice without examination to a person
19 licensed in another state if the board determines that:
20 (a) the other state's license standards at the time of application to this state are substantially
21 equivalent to or greater than the standards in this state; and
22 (b) there is no reason to deny the license under the laws of this state governing the profession or
23 occupation.
24 (2) The license may be issued if the applicant affirms or states in the application that the applicant
25 has requested verification from the state or states in which the person is licensed that the person is currently
26 licensed and is not subject to pending charges or final disciplinary action for unprofessional conduct or
27 impairment. If the board or its screening panel finds reasonable cause to believe that the applicant falsely
28 affirmed or stated that the applicant has requested verification from another state, the board may summarily
- 2 - Authorized Print Version – ****

