1 suspend the license pending further action to discipline or revoke the license. (1) Except as provided in 37-1-
2 147, an applicant for licensure by endorsement must have an active license in good standing from a jurisdiction
3 whose license qualifications, measured at the time of application to this state, are substantially equivalent to the
4 license qualifications of this state.
5 (2) For an application regulated by a board, if the board determines that the qualifications in
6 subsection (1) are not substantially equivalent, the board shall determine whether the deficiency can be
7 addressed by the applicant’s actual qualifications and work experience.
8 (3) For an application regulated by a program, if the qualifications in subsection (1) are not
9 substantially equivalent, the department shall determine whether the deficiency can be addressed by the
10 applicant’s actual qualifications and work experience.
11 (3)(4) This section does not prevent a board from entering into a reciprocity agreement with the
12 licensing authority of another state or jurisdiction. Except as provided in Title 37, chapter 39, the The agreement
13 may not permit out-of-state licensees to obtain a license by reciprocity within this state if the license applicant
14 has not met standards that are substantially equivalent to or greater than the standards required in this state as
15 determined by the board on a case-by-case basis.
16 (5) This section does not apply to the licensure of schools or facilities regulated by boards and
17 programs."
